[A] What is PHP: Hypertext Preprocessor ? 

1. PHP is a widely-used, open source scripting language
2. PHP scripts are executed on the server ( Linux, IIS )
3. PHP can generate dynamic page content

<html>
   <p><?php echo $output; ?></p>
</html>

4. PHP can create, open, read, write, delete, and close files on the server
5. PHP can do CRUD ( Create, Read, Update, Delete ) operations on any database most prefer MySQL.
6. PHP runs on various platforms (Windows, Linux, Unix, Mac OS X, etc.)


[B] Installation :

//Example in ubuntu
//apt-get install apache

1. install a web server like Apache or IIS / TOMCAT
2. install PHP
3. install a database, such as MySQL
4. In common install all stacks in a single combo named : XAMPP for Windows, XAMPP for Linux and XAMPP for OS X.
   Please follow this URL to install : https://www.apachefriends.org/download.html

X - Cross Platform
A - Apache
M - MySQL
P - PHP
P - Pearl

//WAMPP

[C] Understand XAMPP or any other Webserver Cofiguration

About XAMPP : It is a simple, light-weighted Apache server that makes it extremely easy for developers to create a local http server with just few clicks.

